<br>
I've also tried playing around with the numbers, and find that I can get a pretty good set for 30 points per item (so moderate overcharging of 99% items), just make sure each item has 1 skill,<br>
1 attribute, and 2 resists on it, with similar mlvls for each slot.<br>
Typical item is +3 blades, +19 str, +7 fire, +6 spirit.<br>
The system punishes you for any item in which 1 slot has more mlvl's than the other 3.<br>
<br>
if you look at our epic armor, all of its pieces are actually better in terms of total adds than what can be done with spellcrafting (ignoring the fact that it had 30% cold resist).  Similarly, legion and dragon drops are also at 100% quality and have more bonuses than can be made with spellcrafting. <br>
<br>
